-- Czechs Plan to Announce Auction of Mobile Frequencies, HN Says
-- B y   L e n k a   P o n i k e l s k a
-- 2012-03-19T08:26:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-19/czechs-plan-to-announce-auction-of-mobile-frequencies-hn-says.html
The Czech Republic’s
telecommunication regulator, or CTU, plans to announce
preliminary conditions for sale of 4G frequencies today,
 Hospodarske Noviny  reported citing CTU’s head Pavel Dvorak.  The regulator, which plans to announce final conditions for
the auction in June, estimates the value of the frequencies at
10 billion koruna ($536 million), the newspaper added.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lenka Ponikelska in Prague at 
 lponikelska1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  